<style>
  .return-policy-section {
    padding-top: 80px;
    padding-bottom: 100px;
  }

  .return-policy {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--page-width-padding, 20px);
  }

  .return-policy__eyebrow {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #e7cc87;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .return-policy__heading {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 4vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: rgb(var(--color-foreground));
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }

  .return-policy__lead {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.7);
    margin: 0 0 3.5rem;
  }

  .return-policy__block {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.08);
  }

  .return-policy__block:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .return-policy__block-heading {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: rgb(var(--color-foreground));
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
  }

  .return-policy__block-heading .tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    vertical-align: middle;
    margin-left: 0.6rem;
    position: relative;
    top: -2px;
  }

  .return-policy__block-heading .tag--free {
    background: rgba(46, 160, 77, 0.12);
    color: #2ea04d;
    border: 1px solid rgba(46, 160, 77, 0.3);
  }

  .return-policy__block-heading .tag--fee {
    background: rgba(231, 204, 135, 0.12);
    color: #e7cc87;
    border: 1px solid rgba(231, 204, 135, 0.3);
  }

  .return-policy p {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.75);
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
  }

  .return-policy ul {
    margin: 0.8rem 0 1.4rem;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .return-policy ul li {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.75);
    padding: 0.4rem 0 0.4rem 1.8rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .return-policy ul li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #e7cc87;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .return-policy__note {
    background: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.08);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.8rem 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .return-policy__note p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.6);
  }

  .return-policy__cta {
    margin-top: 3.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: 3rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.08);
  }

  .return-policy__cta p {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.65);
  }
</style>

<div class="return-policy-section color-{{ section.settings.color_scheme }} gradient">
  <div class="return-policy">

    <span class="return-policy__eyebrow">Buyer Protection</span>
    <h1 class="return-policy__heading">Return Policy</h1>
    <p class="return-policy__lead">I stand behind every guitar I sell. Here's exactly how returns work — no fine print, no runaround.</p>

    <div class="return-policy__block">
      <h2 class="return-policy__block-heading">
        Not as described or damaged in shipping
        <span class="tag tag--free">Free</span>
      </h2>
      <p>If what shows up doesn't match the listing — condition, specifications, or anything else I documented — I'll make it right. No argument, no hassle.</p>
      <p>Contact me within <strong>3 days of delivery</strong> and I'll arrange a full refund including return shipping. Once the guitar is back and confirmed in its original condition, you'll receive a complete refund to your original payment method.</p>
      <p>This is the kind of seller I want to buy from, so it's the kind of seller I'm going to be.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="return-policy__block">
      <h2 class="return-policy__block-heading">
        Changed your mind
        <span class="tag tag--fee">15% restocking fee</span>
      </h2>
      <p>I understand it happens. If you'd like to return a guitar because it's not the right fit, I'll work with you — under these conditions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact me within <strong>3 days of delivery</strong></li>
        <li>Guitar must be returned in the exact same condition it shipped — no new wear, damage, or missing components</li>
        <li>A <strong>15% restocking fee</strong> applies to cover my time, relisting costs, and original shipping</li>
        <li>Return shipping is the buyer's responsibility</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Once the guitar arrives and I've confirmed its condition, I'll issue a refund of the purchase price minus the restocking fee.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="return-policy__block">
      <h2 class="return-policy__block-heading">How to start a return</h2>
      <p>Reach out through the <a href="/pages/contact" style="color: #e7cc87;">contact page</a> before shipping anything back. Include your order number and a brief description of the issue and I'll get back to you quickly with next steps.</p>
      <p>Returns sent without prior authorization may not be accepted.</p>

      <div class="return-policy__note">
        <p>If you have questions about a guitar before buying — condition, playability, specs, what's included — just ask. I'd rather answer ten questions upfront than deal with a return after.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="return-policy__cta">
      <p>Questions about an order or a return?</p>
      <a href="/pages/contact" class="button">Contact Me</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Return Policy",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "section",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "color_scheme",
      "id": "color_scheme",
      "label": "Color scheme",
      "default": "scheme-1"
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Return Policy"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
